## Vercel Web Analytics Installation

Successfully installed and configured Vercel Web Analytics for this Next.js project.

### Changes Made

#### 1. Package Installation
- **File Modified**: `package.json`
- **Action**: Added `@vercel/analytics` version `^2.0.1` to dependencies
- **Package Manager**: Used `bun` (project's package manager)

#### 2. Analytics Component Integration
- **File Modified**: `app/layout.tsx`
- **Actions**:
  - Added import: `import { Analytics } from "@vercel/analytics/next";`
  - Added `<Analytics />` component at the end of the `<body>` tag, after the provider components
  
### Implementation Details

Following the official Vercel Web Analytics documentation (fetched from https://vercel.com/docs/analytics/quickstart), I:

1. ✅ Installed the `@vercel/analytics` package using bun (the project's package manager)
2. ✅ Imported the Next.js-specific Analytics component from `@vercel/analytics/next`
3. ✅ Added the `<Analytics />` component to the root layout file
4. ✅ Placed it at the end of the body tag to avoid interfering with existing providers
5. ✅ Preserved all existing code structure and functionality

### Files Changed
- `app/layout.tsx` - Added Analytics import and component
- `package.json` - Added @vercel/analytics dependency
- `bun.lock` - Updated with new dependency (lock file)

### Verification
- ✅ Build completed successfully with no errors
- ✅ TypeScript compilation passed
- ✅ Linter ran successfully (no new errors introduced)
- ✅ All existing functionality preserved

### Next Steps for Deployment

To enable Web Analytics on Vercel:
1. Deploy this application to Vercel
2. Navigate to your project's Analytics tab in the Vercel dashboard
3. Click the "Enable" button to activate Web Analytics

Once enabled, Vercel will automatically track visitor data and page views.
